ClassDecl.Name: GuiTextBoxAutoCompleteBase
ClassDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>The base class of text box auto complete controller.</summary> </Document>

VarDecl.Name: tag
VarDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Tag object for any purpose, e.g., data binding.</summary> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetAutoCompleteControl
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the auto complete control that will be installed in a popup to show candidate items.</summary> <returns>The auto complete control.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetListControl
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the list control storing candidate items.</summary> <returns>The list control. It should be inside the auto complete control, or the auto complete control itself.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SetSortedContent
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Store candidate items in the list control.</summary> <param name="items">Candidate items.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetItemCount
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the numbers of all stored candidate items.</summary> <returns>The number of all stored candidate items.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetItemText
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the text of a specified item.</summary> <param name="index">The index of the item.</param> <returns>The text of the item.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GuiTextBoxAutoCompleteBase
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Create an auto complete.</summary> <param name="_autoCompleteControlProvider">A auto complete control provider. Set to null to use a default one.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: IsListOpening
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the list state.</summary> <returns>Returns true if the list is visible.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: OpenList
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Notify the list to be visible.</summary> <param name="startPosition">The text position to show the list.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SetListContent
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Set the content of the list.</summary> <param name="items">The content of the list.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetListStartPosition
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the last start position when the list is opened.</summary> <returns>The start position.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SelectPreviousListItem
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Select the previous item.</summary> <returns>Returns true if this operation succeeded.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SelectNextListItem
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Select the next item.</summary> <returns>Returns true if this operation succeeded.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: ApplySelectedListItem
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Apply the selected item into the text box.</summary> <returns>Returns true if this operation succeeded.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetSelectedListItem
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the selected item.</summary> <returns>The text of the selected item. Returns empty if there is no selected item.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: HighlightList
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Highlight a candidate item in the list.</summary> <param name="editingText">The text to match an item.</param> </Document>
